INSERT INTO `about_universities` VALUES (1,1,'University of Ibadan (UI)','Ibadan, Nigeria',1948,'The University of Ibadan (UI) stands as a prominent public research institution located in Ibadan, Nigeria. Established in 1948 as University College Ibadan under the University of London umbrella, it gained autonomy in 1962, becoming the oldest degree-awarding institution in Nigeria. With a rich history, UI has significantly shaped the political, industrial, economic, and cultural landscape of Nigeria through its extensive graduate network. The enduring impact and influence of the University of Ibadan have solidified its reputation as one of the foremost and prestigious universities in Africa.'),(2,2,'University of Lagos (UNILAG)','Lagos, Nigeria',1962,'The University of Lagos, commonly referred to as UNILAG, stands as a prominent public research institution situated in Lagos, Nigeria, established in 1962. As one of the pioneer universities in Nigeria, UNILAG has earned its place among the top global institutions in various education rankings. With three campuses strategically located in the heart of Lagos, two at Yaba (the main campus in Akoka and a newly established campus at the former school of radiography), and its college of medicine based in Idi-Araba, Surulere, UNILAG encompasses diverse academic landscapes. The main campus, bordered by the Lagos lagoon, sprawls across 802 acres of land. UNILAG, a hub of education excellence, annually welcomes over 9,000 undergraduate students and boasts a total enrollment exceeding 57,000 students.'),(3,3,'University of Nigeria, Nsukka (UNN)','Nsukka, Enugu State, Nigeria',1960,'The University of Nigeria, commonly known as UNN, stands as a federal institution situated in Nsukka, Enugu State, in the Eastern region of Nigeria. Established by Nnamdi Azikiwe in 1955 and officially inaugurated on October 7, 1960, UNN boasts three campuses in Enugu State—Nsukka, Enugu, and Ituku-Ozalla—along with an Aba campus in Abia State. As the pioneering fully indigenous and autonomous university in Nigeria, modeled after the American educational system, the University of Nigeria holds a significant place in the country\'s academic history. It proudly carries the distinction of being Africa\'s first land-grant university and is counted among the top five reputable universities in Nigeria. The institution houses 15 faculties and hosts 102 academic departments, providing a diverse academic landscape. Offering a broad spectrum of education, UNN features 108 undergraduate programs and 211 postgraduate programs, contributing substantially to the educational richness of the region.'),(4,4,'Obafemi Awolowo University (OAU)','Ile-Ife, Nigeria',1962,'Obafemi Awolowo University (OAU) is a comprehensive public institution located in Ile-Ife, Nigeria. Established in 1962, the university is named after Chief Obafemi Awolowo, a prominent Nigerian nationalist, statesman, and the first premier of the Western Region of Nigeria. OAU is renowned for its commitment to academic excellence, research, and community development. The university\'s sprawling campus is set on a vast expanse of land, providing a conducive environment for learning and research. OAU offers a wide range of undergraduate and postgraduate programs across various disciplines, contributing significantly to the intellectual and socio-economic development of Nigeria and beyond.'),(5,5,'Ahmadu Bello University (ABU)','Zaria, Nigeria',1962,'Ahmadu Bello University (ABU) is a federal university located in Zaria, Nigeria. Established in 1962, ABU is named after Sir Ahmadu Bello, the Sardauna of Sokoto and the first premier of the Northern Region of Nigeria. The university is committed to providing quality education, research, and community service. ABU\'s main campus in Samaru, Zaria, is a hub of academic and cultural activities. The university offers a diverse range of undergraduate and postgraduate programs across various faculties and institutes. With a focus on producing well-rounded graduates, ABU contributes significantly to the development of skilled professionals and leaders in Nigeria and beyond.'),(6,6,'University of Ilorin (UNILORIN)','Ilorin, Nigeria',1975,'The University of Ilorin (UNILORIN) is a federal university located in Ilorin, Nigeria. Established in 1975, UNILORIN is known for its commitment to academic excellence, discipline, and moral values. The university\'s main campus is situated on a vast expanse of land, providing a conducive environment for learning and research. UNILORIN offers a wide range of undergraduate and postgraduate programs across various disciplines. The university has earned a reputation for maintaining a stable academic calendar and producing graduates with a strong sense of integrity and professionalism. UNILORIN\'s contributions to education and research have positively impacted the development of Nigeria and the global community.'),(7,7,'Federal University of Technology, Akure (FUTA)','Akure, Nigeria',1981,'The Federal University of Technology, Akure (FUTA), is a federal university located in Akure, Nigeria. Established in 1981, FUTA is dedicated to promoting technological education, research, and innovation. The university\'s main campus is equipped with state-of-the-art facilities and laboratories, fostering a conducive environment for the pursuit of knowledge and the development of technological solutions. FUTA offers a variety of undergraduate and postgraduate programs in engineering, sciences, and technology-related fields. The university\'s commitment to excellence has positioned it as a leading institution in the advancement of technology and the training of skilled professionals in Nigeria and beyond.'),(8,9,'University of Benin (UNIBEN)','Benin City, Nigeria',1970,'The University of Benin (UNIBEN) is a federal university located in Benin City, Nigeria. Established in 1970, UNIBEN is committed to providing quality education, research, and community service. The university\'s main campus is situated on a vast expanse of land, providing a conducive environment for learning and research. UNIBEN offers a wide range of undergraduate and postgraduate programs across various faculties and institutes. The university\'s contributions to education and research have positively impacted the development of skilled professionals and leaders in Nigeria and beyond.'),(9,8,'Nnamdi Azikiwe University, (UNIZIK)','Awka and Nnewi, Anambra State, Nigeria',1991,'Nnamdi Azikiwe University, Awka, also known as UNIZIK or NAU, is a federal university in Nigeria. It consists of two campuses in Anambra State, with its main campus located in Awka, the capital of Anambra State, and another campus in Nnewi. Additionally, there are other campuses of Nnamdi Azikiwe University, Awka, including Agulu in Aniocha local government area and Ifite-Ogwuari in Ayamelum local government area in Anambra State. The university is named after the late Dr. Nnamdi Azikiwe, a prominent figure in Nigerian history.');
